Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Melissa Jane Fitzsimmons in court, defendant Tyree Jaquai Brownlee not in court, in custody.  Mallory R Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Melissa Jane Fitzsimmons in court, defendant Tyree Jaquai Brownlee not in court, in custody.  Mallory R Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for bail/bond hearing. Court hears arguments as to bail. For reasons as set forth on the record, Court modifies bail to $2,500.00 CASH. All other previously ordered terms and conditions of bail to continue. Case is in trial posture, defense counsel requests case be placed on the trial calendar. Any pretrial motions to be filed a week before the final pretrial date. Case adjourned to Branch 35. CASE HEARD IN PRELIM FOR BR. 29:
Defendant Tyree Jaquai Brownlee in court with Attorney Melissa Jane Fitzsimmons; both appear by video.  Mallory Davis appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer Bryant-Povletich. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty. Defense to be heard on bail on the next date. Case is adjourned to Branch 35.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for June 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.
No Contact Order signed and filed.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with ADB (DOB 6/16/13), ALB (DOB 7/31/15), AJB (DOB 2/16/18), AB (DOB 1/17/20), DMS (DOB 8/27/08),
and ALB (DOB 7/17/97).   Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.  The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.

Defendant Tyree Jaquai Brownlee in court with attorney Joan Elizabeth Zawikowski.  Defendant Tyree Jaquai Brownlee in custody.  Sara Waldschmidt-DeSmet appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kiefer Branch 29.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Defense motion to dimiss argued and denied by the court. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
